The `sorry` is in the `Caller` case. We need to prove `⊢ @T b = true` given `h_b : @S b = true`.

The key is to use `h_b` and `equ` (the equivalence of the two distributions). `equ` is `Error.equiv n ... a (S, ...) (T, ...)`.

