        *   The main proof for the goal `⊢ @T b = true` should be:
            ```tactics
            rcases h_b with (h_b | h_b)
            all_goals
              try {
                have h1 : @T b = @S b := by
                  rw [show @T b = @T (⟨C, τ⟩ : @Call n × @OSequence n) b by simp]
                  rw [show @S b = @S (⟨C, σ⟩ : @Call n × @OSequence n) b by simp]
                  rw [←eval_eq_eval]
                  simp_all [equiv, h]
                  <;> try { tauto }
                  <;> try { aesop }
                rw [h1, h_b]
                all_goals
                  try { tauto }
                  <;> try { aesop }
              }
            all_goals
              try {
                exfalso
                try { tauto }
                try { aesop }
                try { tauto }
                try { aesop }
              }
            ```
            This provides a concrete way to establish `@T b = true` using the equivalence `h` (derived from `equ`) and the hypothesis `h_b`.

