This lemma states that if two pairs `(S, σ)` and `(T, τ)` are equivalent with respect to an agent `a` (meaning `S` and `T` produce the same results for `a` when run with `σ` and `τ` respectively), then the result sets of `S` and `T` after `σ` and `τ` must be the same.

